<subSubSection id="E89536ECFFFDFFA2FD6AA692FC0904BB" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="A0306567FFFDFFA2FD6AA692FC0904BB" blockId="18.[714,1243,866,1772]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
DIAGNOSIS: Species of 
<taxonomicName id="678F1EE4FFFDFFA2FB8DA692FBD0038E" authorityName="CHOI" authorityYear="2000" box="[1024,1148,925,948]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Costicoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="92FBB975FFFDFFA2FB8DA692FBD0038E" box="[1024,1148,925,948]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Costicoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be characterized by the forewing with blackish central fascia medially and dorsally greatly tapered, the valva with sclerotized costa and long hairs on the middle of costa, cornuti absent from vesica, and the female genitalia having the corpus bursae with a large, threadlike signum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E89536ECFFFDFFA3FD6AA188FE7005C4" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="20" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="description">
<paragraph id="A0306567FFFDFFA3FD6AA188FE7005C4" blockId="18.[714,1243,866,1772]" lastBlockId="19.[103,632,1423,1769]" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="20" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
DESCRIPTION: Antenna filiform in both sexes. Frons mixed with ochreous and brownish scales. Labial palp short. Legs dark brownish, foreleg tarsal joints distinct with ochreous scales. Metathorax dorsum with blackish tufts. Forewing basally dark brown; basal line dentate, slanted; central fascia blackish, costally bulged; subterminal line whitish, scalloped; apical streak blackish. Hindwing whitish, basally tinged with blackish scales; postmedial line blackish. 
<emphasis id="92FBB975FFFDFFA2FB9AA0A3FB7F05FE" bold="true" box="[1047,1235,1452,1476]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Male genitalia</emphasis>
. Uncus long, basally tapering. Tegumen dome-shaped. Saccus rounded, medially expanded. Anellus lobe long, rod shaped, apically with long hairs. Transtilla thin, round- ed, sclerotized. Valva slender; costa slender, distally with long hairs; sacculus membraneous. Aedeagus cylindrical with large, saclike vesica; cornutus absent. 
<emphasis id="92FBB975FFFDFFA2FBB9A398FCAD06F6" bold="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Female genitalia</emphasis>
. Papillae anales simple. Anterior apophyses about 
<superScript id="57FAC82FFFFDFFA2FCFCA3DEFCD406E5" attach="right" box="[881,888,1745,1759]" fontSize="6" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">3</superScript>
‚ÅÑ 
<subScript id="3C0B6722FFFDFFA2FCF6A3D1FC2806D6" attach="left" box="[891,900,1758,1772]" fontSize="6" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">5</subScript>
length of posterior apophy- ses. Sterigma membraneous, antrum broad, funnel-shaped. Ductus bursae short with a colliculum. Corpus bursae large, subovate, with a long, threadlike signum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E89536ECFFFCFFA4FF09A30AFDBF019E" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="21" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="A0306567FFFCFFA3FF09A30AFE000694" blockId="19.[103,632,1423,1769]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">DISCUSSION: There are four autapomorphies: uncus long (character #12-1); ventral edge of sacculus flat (#27-1); vesica large, saclike (#33-0), signum large, threadlike (#47-3), and wall of corpus bursae with netlike sclerotizations (#48-3).</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A0306567FFFCFFA4FF09A3BAFDBF019E" blockId="19.[103,632,1423,1769]" lastBlockId="20.[138,667,221,508]" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="21" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<taxonomicName id="678F1EE4FFFCFFA3FF09A3BAFE2706F6" authorityName="CHOI" authorityYear="2000" baseAuthorityName="Warren" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[132,395,1717,1740]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Costicoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exangulata">
<emphasis id="92FBB975FFFCFFA3FF09A3BAFE2706F6" box="[132,395,1717,1740]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Costicoma exangulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="678F1EE4FFFCFFA3FDA7A3BAFEC306D3" authority="Hampson" authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1902" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Cidaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deletaria">
<emphasis id="92FBB975FFFCFFA3FDA7A3BAFF5F06D3" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Cidaria deletaria</emphasis>
Hampson
</taxonomicName>
in the male genitalia having long hairs on the costa, but differs in the wing pattern and female genitalia (Choi, 1998a). Results here place 
<taxonomicName id="678F1EE4FFFCFFA3FC62A0C5FB3905DB" authorityName="CHOI" authorityYear="2000" baseAuthorityName="Warren" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[1007,1173,1482,1505]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Costicoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exangulata">
<emphasis id="92FBB975FFFCFFA3FC62A0C5FB3905DB" box="[1007,1173,1482,1505]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">C. exangulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the sister taxon to 
<taxonomicName id="678F1EE4FFFCFFA3FC1FA0E7FBE505C5" box="[914,1097,1512,1535]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Paradysstroma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="corussarium">
<emphasis id="92FBB975FFFCFFA3FC1FA0E7FBE505C5" box="[914,1097,1512,1535]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">P. corussarium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the basal clade is supported by two apomorphic characters: blackish metathorax and thin, round transtilla. This taxon was included in the 
<taxonomicName id="678F1EE4FFFCFFA3FD5EA352FC62064E" authority="(Prout, 1938)" baseAuthorityName="Prout" baseAuthorityYear="1938" box="[723,974,1629,1652]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Therini">Therini (Prout, 1938)</taxonomicName>
, but is distinct from other species of 
<taxonomicName id="678F1EE4FFFCFFA3FC0DA375FC7A06AB" baseAuthorityName="Prout" baseAuthorityYear="1938" box="[896,982,1658,1681]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Therini">Therini</taxonomicName>
based on several apomorphic characters (Choi, 1998a): costa of valva strongly sclerotized with long hairs; large saclike vesica without a cornutus; os- tium bursae broad; colliculum present; signum large, threadlike, and wall of corpus bursae with netlike sclerotization. Differences in wing pattern and genitalia separate 
<taxonomicName id="678F1EE4FFFBFFA4FDFBA43AFF5D0153" authorityName="CHOI" authorityYear="2000" baseAuthorityName="Warren" baseAuthorityYear="1909" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Costicoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exangulata">
<emphasis id="92FBB975FFFBFFA4FDFBA43AFF5D0153" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">exangulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from its sister genus 
<emphasis id="92FBB975FFFBFFA4FD8EA45DFF1801BD" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicName id="678F1EE4FFFBFFA4FD8EA45DFF1C01BD" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Paradysstroma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Paradysstroma</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
suggesting a new genus, 
<taxonomicName id="678F1EE4FFFBFFA4FE6FA47FFDF201BD" authorityName="CHOI" authorityYear="2000" box="[482,606,368,391]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Costicoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="92FBB975FFFBFFA4FE6FA47FFDF201BD" box="[482,606,368,391]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Costicoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is only known from northern 
<collectingCountry id="D89825F7FFFBFFA4FE42A482FDA3019E" box="[463,527,397,420]" name="India" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">India</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E89536ECFFFBFFA4FF2AA4A5FE1F01C6" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="A0306567FFFBFFA4FF2AA4A5FE1F01C6" blockId="20.[138,667,221,508]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
ETYMOLOGY: The name refers to long hairs on the costa in the male genitalia, 
<collectingRegion id="624BAB85FFFBFFA4FDD5A4C8FD3601E4" box="[600,666,455,478]" country="New Zealand" name="West Coast" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Costa</collectingRegion>
(
<emphasis id="92FBB975FFFBFFA4FF1EA4EAFF7B01C6" box="[147,215,485,508]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<collectingRegion id="624BAB85FFFBFFA4FF1EA4EAFF7B01C6" box="[147,215,485,508]" country="New Zealand" name="West Coast" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Costa</collectingRegion>
</emphasis>
) + Hairs (
<taxonomicName id="678F1EE4FFFBFFA4FED0A4EAFE0E01C6" box="[349,418,485,508]" class="Leotiomycetes" genus="Coma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Phacidiales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="92FBB975FFFBFFA4FED0A4EAFE0E01C6" box="[349,418,485,508]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Coma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
